    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-08-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Newport, R. I.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received August 8.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Foster</hi>: I have just received a telegram from
                    Sir John Abbott, the prime minister of the Dominion, in which he informs me that
                    the canal toll question will receive the further consideration of the Canadian
                    Government. The members of the cabinet are, however, scattered all over the
                    country, Sir John himself having only returned, two days ago from, a fortnight’s
                    stay up the Restigouche; and, as so grave a question will necessitate a full
                    meeting of the cabinet, he fears that it will be impossible to arrive at a final
                    decision for a week or ten days longer.</p>
                <p>While much regretting this delay, I venture to express the hope that no further
                    action will be taken by the United States Government in the matter, until I
                    shall have received the answer of the Canadian Government.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Michael H. Herbert.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
